Class DeviceDescriptor

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      opera.discovery.DeviceDescriptor

public final class DeviceDescriptor
extends com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject

Metadata about a device

A device is most commonly a computer, but can also be cell phones, media centre consoles and the likes. Objects of this class give you access to meta information about the device, such as a name and description and the URL the device is exposed on.

Devices are exposed in a DeviceList object through DiscoveryServer.getNearbyDevices() .

Each device can run zero or more services, exposed in a ServiceList object in getServices().

getUrl

public java.lang.String getUrl()
URL this device is exposed on. This URL points to the root of the device. Use it to generate links to the device, or to generate URLs in XHR calls to it.

Example:

a = document.createElement('a');
a.href = device.getUrl();
a.textContent = device.getName()

getUniteUser

public java.lang.String getUniteUser()
Opera Unite username of the owner of this device. If the owner of this device is not an Opera Unite user, this property will be null.

getUniteDeviceName

public java.lang.String getUniteDeviceName()
Opera Unite device name for this device. If the owner of this device is not an Opera Unite user, this property will be null.

getStatus

public int getStatus()
The availability status of this device.

Typically whether the device is on- or offline. The value of this property is one of ONLINE or OFFLINE. The list of constants expanded may be included in the future to include statuses like "Busy".

Example:

if ( device.getStatus() == DeviceDecriptor.OFFLINE )
{
    widget.showNotification(device.getName() + " has been been switched off.");
}

getServices

public ServiceList getServices()
Services running on this device.

If this device is not running any services, the list is empty.
